formThreeBId.notesToCertificate:
1. Promotors have opened RERA Bank Account at the time of registration of the project. However, due to lake of awareness of bankers as well as promotors, deposit ratio of 70% and 30% was not maintained at the initial stage of the project. But, now onwards all receipt from allottees are deposited in Bank Account pursuant to RERA Rules.
2.  70% of total advance received from customers has been shown as cumulative withdrawal in clause 7 above.
3.  In Annexure to CA Certificate (Form 3A), in the column "Date of Agreement of Sale",  date of Agreement of sale or Date of Sale deed as applicable in particular case is provided.
4.  In Annexure to CA Certificate (Form 3A), some units are booked where payment more than 10% has been receive, however Agreement to sale has not been executed. The management have given explanation that, allottee has given written request to Promotor that allottee is not sure about in whose name document to be executed, so till the name is  finalized do not execute the agreement to sale.
5.  In Annexure to CA Certificate (Form 3A), in the column"Mobile Number of Allottee" as per request of promoters, contact number of Promotor is provided due to security reasons.

physProgressList.reason: The average completion of the project as per architech is approximately 87%, while the same is 89% as per engineer certificate and 84.05% as per CA Certificate, the reason for such difference is the architect and engineer certificate is issued based on physical verification of construction, which CA Certificate is issued based on the verification of books of accounts.

secondly, engineer certificate does not consider land cost and it considers cost incurred while in  CA Certificate land cost as well as construciton cost which is incurred and paid is included so percentage completion shall be different in both certificates.
